  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nThe scope of this issue is to add a shortcut to your contact details (chat key and ENS username) inside the Start New Chat dialogue. This follows recent user research studies and prior experiences where we identified that people have difficulty figuring out what to enter when asked for a chat key or ENS name _and_ expecting to share their details with others also from this location.\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\nA small fixed location button is anchored at the bottom of the screen. After interacting it shows the [same popover](https://www.figma.com/file/aS1ct66VQ6V0cio7vSqS8UoG/Chat?node-id=19775%3A177) with user details that we use for sharing a profile. It reacts to keyboard position.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"399\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-04-14 at 12 08 12\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4932774/114693628-17dcf800-9d1a-11eb-9081-83efb1ae05bc.png\">\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nüëâ  [Figma](https://www.figma.com/file/aS1ct66VQ6V0cio7vSqS8UoG/Chat?node-id=7957%3A169) üëà \r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\nDesign was implemented \r\n\r\nThank you üôè \r\n",
